<br>
The rest of the tree slept. <br>
<br>
She sat and tried to think. Her back was healing. She felt better physically then she had in many a year and while that should have made her glad, it only made her restless to be on her way. <br>
<br>
She had to find her locket.<br>
<br>
She still didn't feel herself. It was if her head was being split in two with strange random thoughts entering in to torment her. Fear. Then happiness, then fear again.  And a deep seated anger that upset all around her. Stormygale couldn't help it though. It was if she were losing her mind. <br>
<br>
She came to a decision. It was time to look for the locket herself. Athene and Saphron and the Shaman had eased her enough so that she could go on her way with little pain, but she had to find that locket and they were not looking. At least they did not know where to even begin to look. The locket pulled at her. It was almost like a tugging at her soul. She would find no rest until she found it. <br>
<br>
She stood up and quietly gathered her gear. There was no need to awaken the rest, for they would only object to her leaving. Tip-toeing out into the kitchen, she grabbed some foodstuffs to tide her over. Then quietly returned to her room, after a stop at her mother's room to grab a few bottles. <br>
<br>
Packing things so the bottles didn't clank wasn't easy, but it was a trick her mother had taught her years ago. How to protect the precious cargo from breakage. They might come in handy in bribes or trades, as they were very rare. <br>
<br>
She would go to the bazaar first, and hide out in the stable. She would wait for the pull of the locket to guide her. Everyone went through the bazaar at some point. She would just have to be patient. <br>
<br>
She made her bed with a final pat, and left a note for the other's. She didn't want to worry them and there really wasn't anyway for them to help her on this quest. Athene and Saphron would just have to accept that. <br>
<br>
Hoping no one  would hear her, she cast the spell for the Nexus and quickly ran into the bazaar. She'd been lucky. At such an early hour, there were very few people about and none took any notice of her. <br>
<br>
Doom greeted her with a loud neigh and a nussle, and didn't mind at all as she made herself comfortable in his stall. The tall white stallion would act as a body guard. She tried to bribe the little white mare on one side to be silent with carrots, as she knew the pretty little thing belonged to Saphron. The huge tan on the other side she did not know, but assumed it looked to a troll or an ogre for it's master. Poor beast. She fed it a carrot too.<br>
<br>
Now to wait. She settled back in the  straw and chewed on a hunk of bread. One of these days, the new owner of the locket would wander through and she'd have him or her. She wondered if it was the rogue from Skyshrine, or if he had sold it to a new owner. Well she would find out.  Time would tell. <br>
<br>
She picked her teeth on a stalk of hay and waited.  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=758233">
