<br>
With that Kandiya starred right at the little woman. &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>That</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> eh?  Well that has a name.  My name is Kandiya Holytears.  I was not expecting such an exciting welcome,&quot; as Kandiya nodded and tried to hide the evil smirk.  Kandiya understood the uneasy feelings that everyone had twards dark elves.  Though she had her own troubles at hand with her kind she knew she was not here to have a dispute over such petty things.<br>
<br>
Kandiya took a deep breath.  &quot;I came.....well I should say it called me here.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>It</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.....what do you mean <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>it</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> called you here,&quot; as the taller human blurted out.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm sorry I don't mean to be rude, but I don't know your names.  I have seen your faces many times and I would like to put a name to the faces finally.&quot;  Kandiya wanted to flee, she was terrified, trying to be bold was not her strong point.<br>
&quot;Before we continue we must move, we are not safe here,&quot; the fear in Kandiya's eyes almost put a chill down there backs.<br>
<br>
&quot;I see no point in going anywhere with you,&quot; bosted the small woman.<br>
<br>
&quot;Please, I will gladly tell my story.  But we are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NOT</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> safe here.  We must move now.  Please take us to The Plane of Knowledge.  I know it's safe there.  Please I beg of you......please,&quot;  Kandiya was on her hands and knees at this point.<br>
